{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"LocalProcess"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"overview","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"MacLocalTerminalView"},{"type":"text","text":" is an example of this, it is a subclass of the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"MacTerminalView"},{"type":"text","text":" NSView, and it connects that view to the local system, providing a complete"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"terminal emulator connected to running local commands."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When you create an instance of "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"LocalProcess"},{"type":"text","text":", you provide a delegate that is used to notify"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"your application when data is received from the lcoal process, to request the desired window size"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"that you would like to give to the child process, and when the process terminates."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Once you create this instance, you can start a child process by calling the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"startProcess"},{"type":"text","text":" method"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"which will start the process.   You can then send data to this underlying process using the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"send(data:)"},{"type":"text","text":" method, and you will receive the output on the provided delegate with the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"dataReceived(slice:)"},{"type":"text","text":" method."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Received data is dispatched via the queue that you provide in the LocalProcess constructor, if none"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"is provided, this will default to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"DispatchQueue.main"},{"type":"text","text":".  Generally, this is a good default, but if you"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"have your own main loop or a different dispatching system, you will need to pass your own (for example,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"HeadlessTerminal"},{"type":"text","text":" implementation in the test suite does this."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"terminate"},{"type":"text","text":" call will send the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SIGTERM"},{"type":"text","text":" signal to the child process."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"shellPid"},{"type":"text","text":" property has the PID for the child process, and this can be used to send signals"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to it using the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"kill"},{"type":"text","text":" API."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"childfd"},{"type":"text","text":" property has the Unix file descriptor for the primary side of the created pseudo-terminal."}]}]}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"sections":[],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/swiftterm\/localprocess"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/SwiftTerm\/documentation\/SwiftTerm\/LocalProcess","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"This class provides the capabilities to launch a local Unix process, and connect it to a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Terminal"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"class or subclass."}],"kind":"symbo